    "Newton Upper Falls Chestnut Hill Waban and the town of Wellesley Give me the tiplll do the rest Edward Reynolds Newton Highlands Mass Rather a brilliant idea when you come to think of it The military show at the Madison Square Garden was a grand success both in high merit and financial returns Its success was largely due to the admirable press work of Charles Chamberlain He is a hustler Mine ancient and revered friend Teddy Eiker who edits and publishes the National Advertiser is more than ordinarily mysteri ous in his editorial expressions this week He says that I have taken up with Mr Bok then indulges in a swipe at Mr Lee Starke over my shoulders Teddys refer ence to the much criticised special agent must mean Starke because Teddy has been having hysteria concerning him for some time and then complains that his editorial stomach is out of order He says that he has nausea Now nausea is produced by many causes It is stated as an historical fact that an eminent English statesman was subject to violent mat de mer every time he looked at a mirror I feel that way sometimes when I read the"
